Apache Spark is an open-source distributed data processing engine 
used to process large amounts of data very quickly.


With Apache Spark:

The data is split into smaller pieces.
Those pieces are processed simultaneously by many computers.
The same job might finish in 10–15 minutes (depending on the cluster).

This is called parallel processing.



========================



what is Databricks?

Databricks is a cloud-based data analytics and AI platform built on Apache Spark. It helps organizations store, process, analyze, and build machine learning and AI solutions using large amounts of data.



======================

A Catalog is a top-level container that organizes and stores schemas (databases) in Databricks.